org.jmc.NBT
Class NBT_Tag

java.lang.Object
  org.jmc.NBT.NBT_Tag
Direct Known Subclasses:
TAG_Byte, TAG_Byte_Array, TAG_Compound, TAG_Double, TAG_End, TAG_Float, TAG_Int, TAG_Int_Array, TAG_List, TAG_Long, TAG_Short, TAG_String
public abstract class NBT_Tag
extends java.lang.Object

Notch's Binary Tag class. This is the main NBT class defining the minimum requirements of other tags and containing the main loading/saving routines.

Author:
danijel

make

public static NBT_Tag make(java.io.InputStream is)
                    throws java.lang.Exception
Main loading routine. Reads the tag starting from the current point in the input stream. If the tag is a collection, it also recursively reads the internal items.

Parameters:
is - input stream located at the start of the tag
Returns:
tag object
